WEBVTT

01:38.080 --> 01:40.480
EPISODE 29

01:41.200 --> 01:43.560
Coming...

01:48.840 --> 01:49.800
Who is it?

01:52.280 --> 01:54.760
K.O.? What are you doing here?

01:57.520 --> 02:00.040
- Working the back channels.
- What?

02:05.240 --> 02:06.280
It's so messy.

02:08.440 --> 02:10.199
I only moved in a few days ago.

02:10.280 --> 02:11.680
I haven't had time to tidy up.

02:15.960 --> 02:17.600
How do you know where I live?

02:22.160 --> 02:23.320
Nothing here?

02:34.200 --> 02:35.480
What are you doing?

02:41.240 --> 02:45.120
Get dressed. Go to the grocery store.
Get the things on the list.

02:47.080 --> 02:51.160
Wok, pan, rice cooker,

02:51.240 --> 02:56.200
- spatula, Chinese 'crape' press?
- Crepe.

02:58.000 --> 03:01.520
Soy sauce, corn oil, chicken powder...

03:02.320 --> 03:05.480
- Are you going to cook here?
- Yes.

03:07.560 --> 03:09.360
I'll go to the store, and you?

03:12.040 --> 03:12.920
Prep ingredients.

03:17.400 --> 03:19.560
What's a Chinese crepe press?

03:20.680 --> 03:24.600
Should the spatula be wooden, metal
or stainless steel?

03:26.080 --> 03:26.920
I'll go with you.

03:45.640 --> 03:49.040
The cookware needs washing.
It might take longer.

03:51.520 --> 03:54.480
Keep yourself busy.
Come out and eat in two hours.

03:58.840 --> 04:00.480
This is so weird.

04:01.200 --> 04:03.440
Will he be gone, when I wake up?

04:10.560 --> 04:11.840
It smells amazing!

04:14.680 --> 04:17.480
Egg Yolk Chicken Wings,
Stir-fried Mitten Crab,

04:19.959 --> 04:21.360
Sichuan Boiled Fish,

04:22.360 --> 04:25.080
Stir-fried Sticky Rice Cakes,
Eggplant with Minced Pork!

04:25.280 --> 04:26.880
All of my favorite dishes!

04:28.640 --> 04:29.480
Wash your hands.

04:46.840 --> 04:47.680
Is it good?

04:49.400 --> 04:50.800
It's so yummy!

04:53.200 --> 04:56.960
K.O., you're such a Renaissance man.
Who knew?

04:57.040 --> 05:00.120
This top hacker used to be a chef!

05:01.600 --> 05:04.520
What a legend! Compared to you,

05:04.720 --> 05:08.240
I suddenly find myself a little mediocre.

05:12.720 --> 05:16.160
Where did you go to college, K.O.?

05:18.920 --> 05:21.240
- Nine years of compulsory education.
- What?

05:23.640 --> 05:27.000
I lost all of my family at age 14.

05:28.200 --> 05:30.800
No money, no further education.

05:33.240 --> 05:35.880
Well, you've done great for yourself.

05:36.120 --> 05:39.840
You're much better off
than college graduates like us.

05:40.800 --> 05:42.920
You may have lost to Nai once,

05:43.520 --> 05:46.400
but it had nothing to do with ability.
It's because you have noble character.

05:47.800 --> 05:48.640
I know.

05:51.720 --> 05:52.920
I was being courteous.

05:58.120 --> 06:01.200
So satisfied! So happy!

06:10.360 --> 06:12.800
- I plan on moving in.
- What?

06:16.080 --> 06:22.080
I cook. I do dishes. I mop the floor.
I do the laundry.

06:23.120 --> 06:25.840
I do everything.
Do you want me to live here?

06:27.920 --> 06:28.760
Yes.

06:55.000 --> 06:56.200
Nice!

06:59.560 --> 07:00.720
Do you want this car?

07:00.800 --> 07:01.840
- Get in, Mei.
- Okay.

07:02.280 --> 07:03.320
Put away my bag.

07:04.760 --> 07:09.200
Mei, whatever happened
to fair competition?

07:09.640 --> 07:12.840
You just decided to listen to
the back channel for K.O.!

07:13.800 --> 07:15.120
He cooks, cleans and does the washing.

07:15.200 --> 07:17.240
- Can you do that? Huh?
- I...

07:18.320 --> 07:19.680
My hands are precious.

07:19.760 --> 07:22.160
I couldn't possibly do those chores.

07:22.240 --> 07:24.280
Then shut up and get in the car. Come on!

07:24.360 --> 07:25.960
- Let's hit the road!
- Come on!

07:26.800 --> 07:28.720
You go ahead. I'm picking up Weiwei.

07:29.520 --> 07:31.080
- Let's go together!
- Together!

08:11.040 --> 08:13.040
Get in, Ms. Weiwei.

08:25.120 --> 08:27.200
What an entourage!

08:27.360 --> 08:28.600
They insisted.

08:30.720 --> 08:32.760
I should've met you at the office.

08:32.840 --> 08:33.919
This is too conspicuous.

08:34.720 --> 08:38.240
Don't worry, it's no more conspicuous than
your parents-in-law taking you to school.

08:42.640 --> 08:44.000
You're quite right.

08:44.320 --> 08:45.240
But whose doing was that?

08:48.800 --> 08:49.640
Seat belt.

09:45.800 --> 09:46.680
Slow down.

09:57.560 --> 09:58.720
- Pass him?
- Yep.

10:33.840 --> 10:35.440
What is it? Are we out of gas?

10:35.800 --> 10:39.120
I just remembered,
they only know the name of the mountain.

10:39.520 --> 10:41.480
They don't know the exact location.

10:43.880 --> 10:45.040
Let them wait.

10:46.040 --> 10:48.000
We won't have much time alone
in the next two days.

10:50.160 --> 10:52.640
It's okay.
I like hanging out with everyone.

10:54.120 --> 10:55.280
I meant...

11:16.880 --> 11:18.520
- Are they here?
- What's going on?

11:18.600 --> 11:20.320
I can't get through.

11:20.600 --> 11:22.920
You can't get through? Try again.

11:24.800 --> 11:29.080
- Is it ringing?
- Here they are!

11:33.840 --> 11:36.000
Bro, you're finally here.

11:36.080 --> 11:38.280
What's wrong? You drove so slowly
and didn't answer your phone.

11:42.440 --> 11:45.360
Ms. Weiwei, what's the matter?
Why are you so flushed?

11:47.520 --> 11:50.960
There was no reception. Let's go.

11:53.280 --> 11:54.360
- Come on!
- Let's go.

11:54.560 --> 11:56.600
Let's go...

11:58.440 --> 12:03.520
The air is so nice and clean!
Do you feel it?

12:05.480 --> 12:07.880
The swimming pool is huge!

12:07.960 --> 12:10.920
Nai, when did you discover
such a great place?

12:11.400 --> 12:12.880
It was an accident.

12:14.840 --> 12:17.960
Let Weiwei pick a room first,
then you guys can pick.

12:18.360 --> 12:19.200
Sure.

12:19.280 --> 12:22.160
I'm calling dibs.
I want the room across from the pool.

12:22.240 --> 12:23.720
Nobody fight me for it.

12:24.040 --> 12:25.000
Who's fighting?

12:30.360 --> 12:33.200
Mr. K.O. and others are swimming.
Won't you go take a look?

12:33.720 --> 12:36.160
Living by the sea doesn't mean
one can swim.

12:36.240 --> 12:38.680
I only know how to eat fish.

12:41.400 --> 12:42.240
All right.

12:42.320 --> 12:45.680
This is good enough.
Let's go watch them swim.

12:47.320 --> 12:48.840
Only because you insist.

12:49.640 --> 12:51.520
Fine... Let's go...

12:51.600 --> 12:53.760
I insist, let's go watch them swim.

12:58.800 --> 12:59.640
Come on!

13:05.880 --> 13:09.080
You're just swimming back and forth.

13:09.160 --> 13:11.120
What's the fun in that? Let's race.

13:12.280 --> 13:13.920
Why don't we have them race?

13:14.000 --> 13:15.960
Sure...

13:17.840 --> 13:20.200
I have to warn you beforehand,

13:20.280 --> 13:22.320
Nai is the inter-school swimming champion.

13:24.600 --> 13:27.720
Don't you know there's always someone
who's better?

13:27.800 --> 13:29.080
Look at this body.

13:29.160 --> 13:32.200
He's clearly the champion type. See?

13:32.280 --> 13:33.560
Body?

13:34.600 --> 13:37.240
Mei, you sure have sharp eyes.

13:37.320 --> 13:38.160
Of course!

13:39.440 --> 13:40.760
Mr. Girly?

13:42.160 --> 13:44.080
Why do you look so proud,
when K.O. is praised?

13:45.400 --> 13:46.240
What's it to you?

13:48.480 --> 13:49.320
Are you game?

13:53.800 --> 13:54.640
Sure.

13:54.800 --> 13:57.720
Come on... Let's place bets.

13:58.480 --> 14:00.560
- I bet Lord will win.
- I bet K.O.

14:00.640 --> 14:01.680
I'll be the referee.

14:02.000 --> 14:03.360
Okay, let's do this.

14:04.360 --> 14:05.480
Are you ready?

14:08.280 --> 14:09.120
Get set...

14:22.360 --> 14:23.200
Go!

14:33.480 --> 14:35.560
- Go, Xiao Nai!
- Go!

14:35.640 --> 14:40.160
Go, Lord...

14:41.360 --> 14:44.840
Go, Lord...

14:44.920 --> 14:46.160
- Come on...
- Go!

14:46.800 --> 14:49.720
Faster! Go, K.O., go!

14:49.800 --> 14:52.640
Go, Lord...

15:00.960 --> 15:02.000
Hurry!

15:03.480 --> 15:05.440
Go, Lord...

15:09.120 --> 15:11.920
I hereby declare,
winner of the first round is Nai!

15:16.400 --> 15:18.480
Mr. Girly, I win.

15:18.560 --> 15:20.440
It didn't count... Let's race again.

15:20.520 --> 15:21.680
I'll win the next round.

15:22.720 --> 15:23.560
Again?

15:26.440 --> 15:27.400
Another round.

15:28.320 --> 15:30.960
If I don't win, I can't barbecue.

15:33.400 --> 15:34.240
Okay.

15:36.240 --> 15:37.080
Get set...

15:59.320 --> 16:00.160
Go!

16:05.120 --> 16:08.560
- Faster...
- Ms. Weiwei, you picked first last time.

16:08.640 --> 16:10.080
This time, I bet Nai will win.

16:10.720 --> 16:12.840
Go! Come on!

16:12.920 --> 16:14.480
That leaves me with K.O.

16:16.880 --> 16:17.880
She picked K.O.?

16:30.920 --> 16:32.120
Come on! Hurry!

16:35.920 --> 16:38.240
Go...

16:38.320 --> 16:39.560
Go! Push it!

16:44.320 --> 16:46.480
I hereby declare K.O. winner!

16:46.560 --> 16:48.200
It was so close!

16:49.000 --> 16:50.560
I win again!

16:52.240 --> 16:53.080
You didn't bet I'd win?

16:55.520 --> 16:57.080
I was going to,

16:57.160 --> 16:59.640
but Mr. Girly bet on you first.
I had to bet on K.O.

17:00.560 --> 17:02.520
Nai, did you lose on purpose?

17:02.960 --> 17:05.480
K.O. said, he'd only want to barbecue
if he won.

17:12.640 --> 17:13.920
Is he mad?

17:14.839 --> 17:16.119
Yeah, because you didn't believe in him.

17:19.079 --> 17:20.119
Go talk to him.

17:20.200 --> 17:23.560
What if he doesn't barbecue for us?
Go on!

17:23.640 --> 17:25.200
I've got this. K.O.!

17:31.800 --> 17:33.520
This is nicely grilled.

17:33.760 --> 17:35.040
Here...

17:36.840 --> 17:38.720
Fish is done... Here you go!

17:41.920 --> 17:44.720
- Fish...
- What a hungry pack of wolves!

17:45.840 --> 17:48.920
I sincerely think it'd a shame
for K.O. to be a programmer.

17:49.000 --> 17:51.160
He should be a barbecue chef.

17:51.240 --> 17:53.840
- His future would be much brighter!
- Yes.

17:53.920 --> 17:56.040
True... Mr. K.O.,
you should do your old job.

17:56.120 --> 17:56.960
No.

17:57.880 --> 17:59.960
You won't let him go, boss?

18:00.800 --> 18:03.960
Dining out is troublesome.
We can put a kitchen in the office.

18:05.280 --> 18:07.080
Nai, you're greedy.

18:07.160 --> 18:09.160
This is called, chicken two ways?

18:12.720 --> 18:15.440
Mei, everyone's staring at the food.

18:15.840 --> 18:17.480
You look like you're hungry for the chef!

18:18.600 --> 18:20.760
Drumstick!
I was looking at my chicken drumstick.

18:22.240 --> 18:24.120
K.O., you're so slow.

18:25.320 --> 18:27.240
Here come the drumsticks...

18:28.720 --> 18:31.920
My drumstick, mine...

18:32.000 --> 18:34.520
My drumstick... I stared at it for ages.

18:34.600 --> 18:36.760
It's nearly got my name on it.
My drumstick!

18:36.840 --> 18:38.160
Help...

18:38.400 --> 18:41.000
I've named these Xiao Bei drumsticks.

18:41.080 --> 18:44.520
Nice... Awesome drumsticks.

18:45.840 --> 18:47.000
You're awful.

18:47.560 --> 18:50.480
I'm a big guy,
but I didn't get one drumstick.

18:50.560 --> 18:53.640
Did your fighting value skyrocket
at the sight of food?

18:54.240 --> 18:55.560
K.O., you're too slow,

18:55.640 --> 18:57.760
and you guys are too disorderly.

18:57.840 --> 19:00.840
I think we should have rules
for distributing food.

19:02.160 --> 19:03.520
Why don't we go by capability?

19:03.600 --> 19:06.080
Rock paper scissors,
whoever wins eats first.

19:06.360 --> 19:08.720
That's all luck, not capability.

19:09.120 --> 19:11.000
Anyway, rock paper scissors is so fast.

19:11.080 --> 19:13.160
We play that 100 times
before a drumstick is cooked.

19:13.360 --> 19:16.000
That's true. I have an idea.

19:16.080 --> 19:18.440
We can duel in "A Chinese Ghost Story."

19:19.040 --> 19:20.760
Everyone has an account, right?

19:20.840 --> 19:24.200
Whoever wins eats first.
That's a test of capability.

19:24.280 --> 19:26.640
Gaming geeks! I'll fight you for real!

19:27.280 --> 19:30.040
How? Mrs. Nai is here.

19:30.120 --> 19:33.880
Look at that gluttonous face of hers.
She'll want to join, too.

19:35.680 --> 19:37.800
I vote for gaming duels.
I'll team with Lord.

19:38.800 --> 19:41.840
That reminds me. Nai can't play.

19:41.920 --> 19:43.000
Otherwise he'd get all the drumsticks.

19:43.480 --> 19:45.520
That's true. I second that.

19:45.680 --> 19:46.520
How will I get any food?

19:47.680 --> 19:49.600
Mrs. Nai can win it for you.

19:49.680 --> 19:51.360
It's decided then. Get the laptops.

20:03.080 --> 20:05.320
We're on different servers.
How do we do this?

20:05.640 --> 20:07.600
Let's use our server

20:07.680 --> 20:09.040
and our accounts.

20:09.120 --> 20:11.160
I'll keep score,
and we take turns dueling.

20:11.840 --> 20:13.240
I want to use Lord's character.

20:13.320 --> 20:16.080
Fine, Mrs. Nai.
You want to use an unfamiliar character?

20:16.520 --> 20:19.120
That's certain death for you.
You're asking for it.

20:20.040 --> 20:22.680
How do you know I'd lose,
before we even start?

20:22.760 --> 20:23.720
Let's try it.

20:57.320 --> 20:59.440
- One drumstick.
- Again!

21:00.720 --> 21:01.840
I'll advise her.

21:04.200 --> 21:06.600
You'll advise her? I quit.

21:09.440 --> 21:11.560
Lord opens his mouth and you're scared?

21:13.640 --> 21:17.120
Yugong, your game's up.

21:17.200 --> 21:21.920
- Shame! Are you a man or what, Yugong?
- Shut up! Let's do this then.

21:22.840 --> 21:23.680
Come on!

21:31.000 --> 21:33.960
- Deweaponizer. Disorientor. Speedy Flee.
- Let's see.

21:34.760 --> 21:35.880
Jump up to the combat ring.

21:35.960 --> 21:38.480
Resistance Booster, add blood points.
Create Fox.

21:41.560 --> 21:43.840
Weiwei can keep up with Bro Xiao?

21:44.120 --> 21:46.480
Someone's going down...

21:47.760 --> 21:49.560
Silencer. Group Paralyzer.

21:58.200 --> 22:01.960
Yu Banshan, minus a drumstick.

22:03.280 --> 22:04.480
Why minus a drumstick?

22:05.040 --> 22:07.160
Well, you lost to two people.

22:08.800 --> 22:11.280
Scoundrel! I'll kill you!
Minus a drumstick?

22:12.080 --> 22:13.120
You're a sore loser!

22:13.200 --> 22:14.560
Mrs. Nai... Let me use your character.

22:14.840 --> 22:16.200
I haven't tried yours.

22:16.520 --> 22:17.680
Sure, hold on.

22:17.760 --> 22:19.320
- Let me log in.
- Okay.

22:32.600 --> 22:33.440
Ready, Mrs. Nai?

22:34.560 --> 22:36.440
Hold on, let me read this message.

22:43.640 --> 22:47.000
Luwei Weiwei, you must be curious

22:47.160 --> 22:49.080
why you received this note?

22:49.640 --> 22:53.880
I never thought, before bidding goodbye
to "A Chinese Ghost Story,"

22:53.960 --> 22:57.320
my last note would be to you.

22:58.040 --> 23:01.280
Don't feel troubled.
This is a farewell message.

23:01.560 --> 23:02.960
I don't have other intentions.

23:03.320 --> 23:07.200
There are things on my mind,
that I don't know who I can tell.

23:08.320 --> 23:10.200
Just think of this as a tree hole post.

23:16.040 --> 23:18.880
I, Zhen Shaoxiang,
have been idle all my life.

23:19.120 --> 23:20.760
I've never done anything serious.

23:21.720 --> 23:26.240
I only took part in game development,
after I was provoked,

23:27.520 --> 23:29.600
but I unexpectedly found my passion.

23:30.160 --> 23:33.080
I may lack the knowledge and experience,

23:33.160 --> 23:34.760
but I still gave it all I've got.

23:34.840 --> 23:37.280
I was prepared to fail, actually.

23:37.600 --> 23:41.120
I just never thought
I'd lose so dishonorably.

23:41.760 --> 23:44.400
If I told you, I had no idea about

23:44.480 --> 23:46.160
those underhanded tactics,

23:46.880 --> 23:48.600
would you believe me?

23:49.720 --> 23:52.680
Even so, I'm still very ashamed.

23:53.800 --> 23:57.120
Xiao Nai must despise me now.

23:58.440 --> 24:01.560
The truth is, if I was capable,

24:02.160 --> 24:05.200
my father wouldn't have resorted
to such shady tactics.

24:06.800 --> 24:08.880
I've played this game for years.

24:09.080 --> 24:12.880
Now, I feel like can no longer stay.

24:13.640 --> 24:15.360
Every time I log in,

24:15.640 --> 24:18.600
it reminds me
of that dishonorable experience.

24:19.200 --> 24:22.640
So, I decided to earnestly
learn some things.

24:23.080 --> 24:26.280
I might have you and Xiao Nai
to thank for that.

24:27.560 --> 24:29.600
Finally, please tell Xiao Nai,

24:30.120 --> 24:31.600
one of these days,

24:31.680 --> 24:33.880
I will beat him and make a better game.

24:45.440 --> 24:46.440
Good luck.

24:53.480 --> 24:55.880
I'll be waiting. Xiao Nai.

24:58.520 --> 25:02.680
Ready? Mrs. Nai,
the flowers have wilted while I wait.

25:02.760 --> 25:03.760
It's all yours.

25:04.320 --> 25:06.920
Okay, this is for K.O.'s drumstick.

25:07.000 --> 25:07.840
Who am I dueling?

25:07.920 --> 25:10.560
- Me!
- You? Come on!

25:18.080 --> 25:21.840
All right, now it's time
to announce the results.

25:22.920 --> 25:26.480
Ms. Weiwei, three chicken drumsticks
and ten lamb skewers.

25:26.560 --> 25:28.600
A round of applause!

25:30.200 --> 25:33.320
- Here... Dig in, everyone.
- Hao Mei, two chicken wings.

25:34.960 --> 25:40.560
Yu Banshan, nothing, minus a drumstick.

25:41.480 --> 25:43.440
This doesn't make sense.

25:43.520 --> 25:45.600
I haven't had anything to eat.

25:45.680 --> 25:47.040
You won't even share.

25:47.120 --> 25:49.480
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

25:49.560 --> 25:50.760
We'll go for a walk.

25:51.600 --> 25:54.920
I haven't had dinner, yet,
and you're going on a date?

25:55.600 --> 25:58.240
If we stay any longer,
you'll be hungry all night.

26:22.320 --> 26:24.800
This looks just like
the Sunset Peak in the game.

26:25.560 --> 26:27.120
That's why I brought you here.

26:31.960 --> 26:36.240
I just had a thought.
Once "A New Chinese Ghost Story" is out,

26:36.400 --> 26:39.240
will players in the original game dwindle?

26:39.320 --> 26:41.560
And the game will be canceled?

26:43.560 --> 26:46.720
No, I think it will keep operating.

26:49.400 --> 26:51.400
But "A New Chinese Ghost Story"
will take away many players.

26:51.480 --> 26:54.880
Won't Fengteng shut off the server,
when player numbers drop?

26:56.520 --> 27:00.760
However great the new game is,
some old functions can't be replaced.

27:02.600 --> 27:04.200
Not everyone will leave.

27:05.040 --> 27:06.160
And I remember,

27:06.920 --> 27:10.520
Fengteng promised
to keep the game operating forever.

27:12.120 --> 27:13.600
So they say.

27:14.400 --> 27:19.480
Some games were still canceled,
despite the promise to operate forever.

27:20.640 --> 27:22.000
I can't promise forever,

27:23.560 --> 27:28.240
but it should last until
our kid is able to play the game.

27:29.240 --> 27:30.760
Kid?

27:32.920 --> 27:33.760
That's right.

27:40.920 --> 27:43.280
I want to at least bring the kid
to Red Sparrow Bridge,

27:43.760 --> 27:50.400
let the kid know the first things
we said to each other there.

27:55.120 --> 27:57.840
Yes, Mr. Yixiao Naihe?

27:57.920 --> 27:58.920
Form an in-game marriage with me.

27:59.920 --> 28:02.080
I'll do it. Let's go to the Rock of Lives.

28:15.200 --> 28:17.000
You should've handled this yourself,

28:17.920 --> 28:19.560
but there are too many busybodies around.

28:20.880 --> 28:23.040
I thought it best to get it over with.

28:23.160 --> 28:24.760
We'll brave this world together,

28:24.840 --> 28:26.720
like a pair of wild mandarin ducks.

28:27.640 --> 28:31.960
Wild mandarin ducks?
I remember we were formally married.

28:36.120 --> 28:38.160
Mr. Xiao? What a coincidence!

28:45.840 --> 28:49.080
It's not a coincidence.
I'm waiting for you.

28:56.040 --> 29:00.440
I suddenly feel like
what was troubling me just now

29:00.880 --> 29:02.400
doesn't matter anymore.

29:04.640 --> 29:07.560
Even if the game gets canceled,

29:08.560 --> 29:10.760
the scenery we enjoyed together

29:11.440 --> 29:12.920
and the things we did together

29:13.480 --> 29:16.800
won't erase the memories,
even if the data is erased.

29:20.240 --> 29:25.640
I'll always keep them in my heart.
What about you?

29:29.600 --> 29:31.440
My memory will be better than yours.

30:02.880 --> 30:06.640
TWO YEARS LATER

30:06.720 --> 30:07.560
Welcome to the show, everyone.

30:07.920 --> 30:10.240
Our guest today is quite special.

30:10.320 --> 30:12.080
He may be unfamiliar

30:12.160 --> 30:13.720
to our usual audience.

30:13.800 --> 30:17.040
He is a rising celebrity
in the gaming industry.

30:17.120 --> 30:19.760
Please welcome the producer of
"A New Chinese Ghost Story,"

30:19.840 --> 30:20.680
Xiao Nai.

30:22.080 --> 30:22.920
Hello, everyone.

30:23.360 --> 30:24.400
First of all, congratulations!

30:24.480 --> 30:26.840
Your mobile game and client game
have both won big international awards.

30:26.920 --> 30:27.760
Thanks.

30:28.240 --> 30:30.680
In addition to winning accolades,

30:30.760 --> 30:33.560
these two games also have done
very well commercially.

30:33.880 --> 30:36.040
I just saw the data.

30:36.120 --> 30:38.920
Your mobile game generates
200 million in revenue per month.

30:39.000 --> 30:40.120
For a mobile game,

30:40.200 --> 30:42.280
it's a very rare accomplishment.

30:42.360 --> 30:45.520
The client game also enjoys
record-breaking player numbers.

30:45.600 --> 30:48.440
Did you imagine these games would be
so successful, when you made them?

30:50.400 --> 30:53.080
When our team created these two games,

30:53.400 --> 30:54.920
we were still college students.

30:56.000 --> 30:57.600
At the time, client games and mobile games

30:57.680 --> 30:59.120
weren't as popular as now.

30:59.640 --> 31:02.000
So, we never thought about

31:02.080 --> 31:04.120
how to be successful commercially.

31:04.640 --> 31:07.840
We were only trying to put out
our ideas for gaming.

31:08.520 --> 31:11.200
That's great.
A mobile game and a client game

31:11.280 --> 31:15.520
have made you the most
investment-worthy gaming company.

31:15.600 --> 31:18.240
I hear Fengteng is buying up Zhiyi.
Is it true?

31:20.560 --> 31:23.200
We have product collaboration
with Fengteng.

31:23.280 --> 31:25.040
They're not involved in our financing.

31:26.040 --> 31:27.800
Let's shift gears.

31:27.880 --> 31:31.480
There's a tradition in the industry
to throw shade on the original creator,

31:31.560 --> 31:33.800
but since you're so good-looking,

31:33.880 --> 31:36.880
players only have good things
to say about you.

31:36.960 --> 31:38.280
Are you aware of this?

31:38.640 --> 31:40.920
I think players are nice to me,

31:41.000 --> 31:42.600
because our game is fun.

31:44.120 --> 31:45.520
Here's a reminder.

31:45.600 --> 31:49.080
"A New Chinese Ghost Story" is jointly
produced by us and Fengteng Group.

31:49.160 --> 31:51.680
The president of Fengteng is named
Feng Teng. Very easy to remember.

31:51.880 --> 31:55.240
You're redirecting the attention his way?
Nicely done.

31:55.720 --> 31:58.000
Aside from "A New Chinese Ghost Story,"

31:58.080 --> 31:59.960
will you be launching new games?

32:00.400 --> 32:03.040
We don't have plans to create new games.

32:03.120 --> 32:05.520
Zhiyi's next focus is on cybersecurity.

32:07.400 --> 32:09.400
Lord is still so handsome.

32:09.480 --> 32:12.080
Now the entire world sees
his handsome face.

32:12.160 --> 32:14.480
I suddenly feel a bit possessive.
What should I do?

32:15.920 --> 32:18.680
Weiwei isn't possessive.
Why should you be?

32:20.200 --> 32:22.200
Says who? Don't look!

32:22.280 --> 32:24.840
- So selfish! Let us look.
- Don't stop us.

32:25.160 --> 32:28.400
You can try to stop him
from getting interviewed.

32:29.200 --> 32:31.920
There's no use in stopping him.

32:32.000 --> 32:34.600
He's already been seen at the
"Daydreaming in Jianghu" press conference.

32:35.120 --> 32:38.560
Don't tell me, you contemplated it?
You're too selfish!

32:39.080 --> 32:41.160
I hear your game

32:41.240 --> 32:42.880
is very popular with women,

32:43.240 --> 32:45.880
but you have an all-male staff.

32:45.960 --> 32:48.920
How did you create a game
that's so popular with women?

32:49.800 --> 32:54.320
That's a false rumor.
My fiancée is also on the staff.

32:55.320 --> 32:56.880
- Fiancée?
- Fiancée?

32:56.960 --> 32:58.640
What have you done? Tell us!

32:58.720 --> 32:59.960
Why are you suddenly his fiancée?

33:01.400 --> 33:04.640
- I have no idea.
- Don't lie! Lord proposed to you?

33:04.720 --> 33:06.120
No.

33:07.600 --> 33:08.960
Wait... Could it be...

33:11.760 --> 33:14.320
Do I go work for you after I graduate?

33:15.000 --> 33:15.920
What else?

33:20.200 --> 33:23.000
I've interned at your company
for two summers,

33:23.080 --> 33:25.200
but I've never gotten paid.

33:26.280 --> 33:27.120
Oh.

33:29.200 --> 33:30.040
What does that mean?

33:31.040 --> 33:35.720
It means, no money for you,
but you can take the man.

33:45.840 --> 33:47.920
That counts?

33:48.760 --> 33:52.360
Lord is unbelievable.
You're his girlfriend before you two met.

33:52.920 --> 33:54.720
You're his fiancée, before he proposed.

33:55.800 --> 33:59.240
He's still as cunning as ever.

34:00.320 --> 34:03.280
Weiwei, I'm really worried for you.

34:03.360 --> 34:06.680
There's no way you can beat him
in a battle of wits.

34:06.760 --> 34:10.120
Even in wrestling,
you have no chance against him.

34:10.199 --> 34:12.280
Your status in the family
is cause for concern.

34:13.520 --> 34:14.920
Lord doesn't wrestle.

34:15.679 --> 34:20.320
Silly! I meant
the other kind of wrestling.

34:24.320 --> 34:26.880
- Are you dressed yet, Erxi?
- What kind of wrestling?

34:26.960 --> 34:30.360
- I'm not waiting anymore.
- Wait... I just need to powder my face.

34:30.440 --> 34:33.280
- Hurry up, Erxi.
- Come on!

34:41.360 --> 34:44.080
What do you think? Sexy?

34:45.080 --> 34:50.800
Weiwei, I don't want to take
my graduation photo with her like that.

34:50.880 --> 34:53.440
It's fine...
The photographer won't let her.

34:55.480 --> 34:58.360
What's wrong with your aesthetics?
What? Don't I look nice?

35:24.240 --> 35:25.760
Come on... Gather together.

35:26.320 --> 35:28.400
Professors, take your seats.

35:28.480 --> 35:29.520
My cap is crooked.

35:33.840 --> 35:36.400
You, the tall guy in the middle.

35:36.480 --> 35:39.280
That's right. You, go to the side. Good.

35:40.400 --> 35:41.640
The girl in the bright dress,

35:41.920 --> 35:44.320
hide your dress for me. Okay.

35:45.440 --> 35:48.720
Can't we have some individuality?

35:55.720 --> 35:57.480
Here we go. Get ready.

35:57.600 --> 36:00.880
Three, two, one!

36:02.600 --> 36:03.640
Why are you looking away?

36:03.720 --> 36:06.360
Look at me. Why are you looking away?

36:07.680 --> 36:10.280
Hey, eye-candy! Hide behind the trees.

36:12.200 --> 36:13.320
Come on... Look here.

36:14.160 --> 36:16.680
Three, two, one!

36:19.960 --> 36:21.560
Good. Let's take another one.

36:21.640 --> 36:24.320
Let's be playful for this one. Ready?

36:24.400 --> 36:27.760
Three, two, one!

36:29.960 --> 36:30.920
Very good.

36:31.000 --> 36:34.320
For the third shot,
toss your caps into the air.

36:34.400 --> 36:39.120
Come on. Three, two, one!

36:46.840 --> 36:48.640
Weiwei... Get Lord to come.

36:48.720 --> 36:51.320
- I want a photo with him.
- It's her fiancé.

36:52.960 --> 36:54.600
Get Dazhong to come, too.

36:55.120 --> 36:56.640
- Get my cap.
- Hurry!

36:57.280 --> 36:58.680
Get my cap.

37:01.520 --> 37:03.880
- How's it going?
- Hey! Take photos for us.

37:03.960 --> 37:05.440
Happy graduation...

37:07.040 --> 37:08.880
So sappy!

37:11.360 --> 37:12.840
Radiant Mr. Xiao,

37:12.920 --> 37:14.760
my roommates want to take photos with you.

37:14.840 --> 37:17.000
Is that okay?

37:17.200 --> 37:20.040
Photos with me?
You'd have to ask my girlfriend.

37:22.560 --> 37:23.400
I thought it was fiancée?

37:24.760 --> 37:26.640
Sorry, my bad.

37:27.040 --> 37:29.560
You'd have to ask my fiancée.

37:33.600 --> 37:35.480
Yes, take photos with them. Let's go.

37:35.560 --> 37:37.840
- What's the hold-up?
- I'll take photos of you two.

37:39.200 --> 37:42.400
- Lord is here.
- Lord, I want photos with you!

37:42.480 --> 37:44.680
- Weiwei!
- Hurry! We want photos, too.

37:47.920 --> 37:50.960
Come on. One, two, three!

37:53.120 --> 37:55.840
- Okay. More?
- Dazhong, take photos for us.

37:56.040 --> 37:58.360
Come on... All four of us. Hurry...

37:59.360 --> 38:00.200
Come...

38:00.840 --> 38:03.440
- Let's step down.
- One, two, three!

38:46.000 --> 38:48.240
Take another photo for me!

38:52.680 --> 38:54.760
They're so heartless!

38:54.880 --> 38:58.160
I only took 200 photos,
and they're impatient.

38:58.240 --> 38:59.200
I'll take a selfie!

39:20.680 --> 39:22.840
I should ask someone
to take a photo for me.

39:26.040 --> 39:28.200
You, there! Can you take a photo for me?

39:42.520 --> 39:44.160
Ms. Stranger,

39:44.240 --> 39:45.760
can you please get down?

39:45.840 --> 39:47.560
Don't tarnish our school's image.

39:48.680 --> 39:51.200
Who's tarnishing our school's image?

39:51.280 --> 39:52.920
What's wrong with
taking graduation photos?

39:54.360 --> 39:58.520
You clean up nice,
but you're still acid-tongued.

40:00.840 --> 40:03.640
The genius of
our foreign languages department

40:03.720 --> 40:06.080
is a tour guide for foreigners now?

40:07.120 --> 40:08.360
Tour guide?

40:10.000 --> 40:13.200
I'm an attaché for foreign guests
of the business delegation to China.

40:16.000 --> 40:19.200
So, you're not even a tour guide.
You're a sidekick!

40:33.320 --> 40:35.640
You hear that? She says I'm lovely.

40:35.800 --> 40:38.520
Forget taking photos for me.

40:39.480 --> 40:41.200
You're so narrow-minded,

40:41.280 --> 40:43.360
you couldn't capture a tenth of my beauty.

40:44.400 --> 40:46.440
Zhao Twoxi, you should be careful.

40:47.800 --> 40:50.920
Why should I be careful? You should...

41:20.440 --> 41:22.480
Where did that rascal Erxi go?

41:23.880 --> 41:27.000
What's going on?
That guy holding Erxi looks familiar.

41:27.080 --> 41:28.440
What's with you? It's Cao Guang!

41:28.520 --> 41:31.200
I hear the foreign languages genius
works at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.

41:38.840 --> 41:44.040
He's incredible for holding
Erxi like that. It's so sensational!

41:44.680 --> 41:46.240
Come here, Weiwei...

41:50.560 --> 41:52.400
Should we go get Erxi back?

41:52.480 --> 41:54.160
Are you silly or what?

41:54.240 --> 41:56.200
Can't you feel

41:56.280 --> 41:59.080
the love hearts floating
around Erxi and Cao Guang?

41:59.880 --> 42:02.040
It's a classic prelude
to a budding romance.

44:44.280 --> 44:46.720
Subtitle translation by Lu Yuhan
